<chapter xml:id="ch-season2" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Season 2: Negative Numbers</title>

  <introduction>
    <p> 
       Negative numbers are used to represent things like temperatures below 0, overdrawn bank accounts, and debts. In this season,
        we'll learn how to perform the five basic math operations (addition, subtraction, multiplication, division, and exponents) on negative numbers.  
      </p>
  </introduction>
